  "text": "The pattern of an increase in immune defence with increasing reserves is based on the state-dependent optimal strategy within a particular environment. A different pattern may emerge if we consider the optimal behaviour for each of a range of environments. For example, figure 3d-f shows that as the variability in food is increased while the mean is kept constant, immune defence decreases (figure 3d ) and energy reserves increase (figure 3 f ). Thus, across environments, there is a negative correlation between reserves and immune defence. This sort of counter-intuitive correlation has been observed in other contexts; across environments there can be a positive correlation between energy reserves and death from predation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
